oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Cumberland County Courthouse
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Exterior of the Cumberland County Courthouse, located in Crossville on Main Street.

It was built with sandstone from the county, and completed in 1905. It was the third courthouse built for the county, the first one dating back to 1857 and the second one to 1886. The building was designed by W. Chamberlain and Company, an architectural firm from Birmingham, Alabama. It has been listed on the National Register of Historic Places since June 17, 1980. The firm is named for Walter Chamberlain, and had an office in Knoxville.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
